items.title: Stocks making the biggest moves premarket: EchoStar, Robinhood, AppLovin, Alibaba and more
items.description: These are some of the stocks posting the largest moves in premarket trading.

items.title: Klarna's IPO will test if it's more than just a one-trick 'buy now, pay later' pony
items.description: Klarna has been attempting to convince the market that it's more of a digital retail bank than a simple buy now, pay later firm.

items.title: Alibaba leads $100 million investment in Chinese humanoid robot startup
items.description: Capital is rushing into humanoids — X Square Robot has completed eight fundraising rounds in less than two years since the startup was founded.

items.title: Nasdaq's listing plans will make it harder for small Chinese companies to go public in the U.S.
items.description: The move comes as tensions between the U.S. and China simmer, and as the Nasdaq faces broader financial market issues.

items.title: Wall Street’s dilemma: How Fed rate cut hopes clashed with slowing jobs growth
items.description: The S&P 500 and Nasdaq both briefly hit record intraday highs Friday before tumbling on a weaker August jobs report.
